    "content": "About Us &mdash; PWI, Inc. in Wichita Kansas USA Company Overview Diversification From Windings to Aircraft Lighting With more than 60 years of experience, PWI is one of the few companies that still creates precision fluxgate magnetometers, coils, and windings in a worldwide marketplace. PWI has also designed and manufactured general aviation lighting for more than 50 years. We also offer engineering and manufacturing services. View Qualifications Product Information 60+ Years in Business ITAR Compliant AS9100 Certified ISO 9001 Certified Since 1963 Company History 1963 Founded in Wichita, Kansas USA by Miklos Lorik Created windings for international customers 1972 First fluorescent light cabin lighting, made in-house 1998 SBA Miklos Lorik &ldquo;Person of the Year&rdquo; 2000 Precision Winding Inc renames as PWI, Inc. 2004 EASA Repair Station approval (Europe) 2008 LED aircraft lighting created NBAA membership 2012 AFAC product approval (Mexico) 2015 ANAC product approval (Brazil) 2016 AS9100 company certification 2019 Robi Lorik becomes CEO/President 2025 ITAR registered, CMMC Level 1 2026 Rick Estes becomes CEO/President Our Standard Quality Policy PWI is committed to delivering exceptional product quality through decades of experience, innovation, and technical expertise. Striving for Excellence For more than 60 years, focus has remained on design excellence, precision manufacturing, regulatory compliance, and continuous improvement across all product lines. Design excellence & manufacturing precision Regulatory compliance (FAA, EASA, UK CAA, Transport Canada) Continuous improvement across all product lines"
