    "url": "led-ice-light.html",
    "content": "LED Ice Light from PWI, Inc. replaces 7079B24 bulbs Home / Aviation Lighting / LED Ice Light FAA-approved LED Aircraft Lighting LED Ice Light Replaces 7079 Bulbs Part Numbers 7310009-000 / 7310045-000 PMA PQ4159CE Supplements 19, 26 - bayonet mount Supplements 24 - threaded mount King Air and Citation Jets Replaces Bulbs: A7079B24, MS25338-7079, 34-007037-01, 900-005-00, WA7079B24 3-Year Warranty Designed and Manufactured in the USA Approved Aircraft Beechcraft Baron 55, 58 Beechjet 400, 400A King Air 90, 100, 200, B200, 300, B300 Airliner / Commuter 99 Cessna Caravan 208, 208B Centurion 210, P210, T210 Conquest II 441 Citation 525 Series Citation Bravo 550 Citation 560 Citation Excel 560XL Citation III 650 Series Citation Sovereign 680 Citation X 750 Overview The PWI LED Ice Light replaces incandescent bulbs A7079B24, MS25338-7079, and WA7079B24. It provides 210 more lumens for faster ice detection and is available with a standard bayonet mount or a threaded mount. The threaded mount eliminates the bayonet socket entirely when sockets are corroded. Long LED life, reduced power draw, and lower generated heat help reduce lens discoloration, cracking, and warping. Email for Pricing Download Product Information 6 photos Bayonet mount Threaded mount option Why Upgrade Brighter LED output improves ice formation detection, using far less power than incandescent bulbs. Installation Available as a bayonet-mount or with a threaded-mount - removing the bulb socket when bayonet sockets are corroded. Product Details System Specs Bayonet Mount Part Number 7310009-000 Threaded Mount Part Number 7310045-000 Voltage 28 Volts DC Output 730 Lumens Power Used 5.6 Watts Current Draw 200 milliamps Operating Temp 54&deg;C Beam Angle FWHM 8 Ambient Temp Operating Range -55&deg;C to +70&deg;C Bayonet Lamp Base BA15S Diameter 1.6 inches (4.1 centimeters) Length 2.37 inches (6.0 centimeters) Weight 56 grams Key Benefits 100,000-hour service Faster ice detection Better aircraft visibility during taxi, takeoff, landing Very low power draw More light, far less generated heat Lower heat reduces lens degradation Direct replacement for incandescent bulb Bayonet or threaded mount Certificate of Conformity available Form 8130-3 available on request Approved Aircraft & Mounting Aircraft model and serial number for quoting or ordering. LED Use - ICE LIGHT Approved Aircraft Beechcraft: Baron 55, 58; Beechjet 400, 400A, 400XP; King Air 90, 100, 200, B200, 300, B300; Airliner/Commuter 99 Series Cessna: Conquest II 441; Caravan 208, 208B; Centurion 210, P210, T210 LED Use - CITATION Cessna: Citation Sovereign 680 (Pylon Flood Light), Citation X 750 (Wing Downwash, Pylon Work, Tail Flood) Replaces A7079B24 MS25338-7079 34-007037-01 900-005-00 WA7079B24 11-15189 11-16661 08-13468 11-01963 PWI LED vs A7079B24 Bulb PWI LED A7079B24 Light Output in Lumens 730 650 Color Temperature 5000K 2700K Power Draw 5.6 Watts 42 Watts Operating Temp 54&deg;C 170&deg;C Operating Hours 100,000 165 Current Draw 200 milliamps 1500 milliamps Also Available More Exterior LED Lighting King Air Ice Light Windows LED Logo Light LED Entry Door / Underwing Light"
